This paper deals with the specification and implementation of human-computer dialogs, which involves natural language processing and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.CL, cs.AI). It also involves software engineering concepts such as design and implementation (cs.SE). The focus on improving user experience and interaction suggests a connection to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the use of programming language concepts and automatic generation of code suggests a connection to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG).
